<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_fc6adb9b-7ba2-44e4-90eb-1d0214e32d53" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>12.4.3</sptc><title id="_396fc04a-f74d-4711-a3a3-5c76b5ca9c93">Chimney construction</title><archive-num>2019: 3.10.7.3</archive-num><subclause id="_1cbcb675-0d06-4042-bb48-e5963c32303b" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_092cf3cf-2bb2-4534-b860-8ad2938dbf46">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The construction of a chimney must comply with <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1807#_c1e7a2da-3ebf-4007-9f08-134efafe0279" id="_dc354b9c-23c4-4343-b6c8-b4427b940372" publishing-id="vol2" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">H1D5</xref> and the following:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_a249068e-0d86-432f-b110-b68468435034">The walls of the chimney above the level referred to in <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/2661_1.7.0.xml#_ef86e29f-51cb-46c5-a25e-413f5188dfba" id="_542c8bd7-f0ff-45fd-89d7-e44a108f024f" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="clause">12.4.2(c)</xref> must be lined internally to a thickness of not less than 10 mm with composition mortar parging.</li><li id="_fa91eabc-8bfe-4549-a8fc-5bbb2db83c9f">The composition mortar in (a) must comply with AS 3700 or AS 4773 except that the mortar must be mixed by volume in the proportions of 1 part cement : 1 part lime : 5 parts sand. </li><li id="_ee61e916-d020-4dc5-a4ae-ce5bb6063c6c">The chimney or flue must terminate not less than 300 mm above the highest part of the building within a horizontal distance of 3.6 m of the chimney or flue (see <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/906_0.7.0.xml#_2e89ef8e-308b-411f-b5a9-81503d82271c" id="_a66c92bb-2c73-490f-ac0f-e2afd0ce3bcc" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 12.4.3</xref>).</li></ol></subclause><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/906_0.7.0.xml" id="_2e89ef8e-308b-411f-b5a9-81503d82271c"><num>12.4.3</num><title id="_12e10753-99e4-4e32-8160-8e2a0fcec25f">Section showing height and position of chimney</title><image alt="Section showing height and position of chimney" height="815" heightdpi="200" href="ERROR_IN_RESOLVING_URI:12-4-3-section-showing-height-and-position-of-chimney.eps" width="1200" widthdpi="200"><image height="815" heightdpi="200" href="C:\Users\bkiem\AppData\Roaming\Quark\XML Author\Temp\media1_f2bc8b2b-72ec-4847-b659-58a7b41ca98b.jpg" width="1200" widthdpi="200"/></image></image-reference><callout id="_2effb4cf-93f7-4228-b1e1-449b53e84901"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><ul outputclass="numbered"><li>The requirements of this Part are to be read in conjunction with the building sealing requirements in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/4234_0.7.0.xml#_09a0cfcb-49e7-4656-a327-9fbd0dbd1672" id="_f1f59511-5b9c-4d03-a601-3b252a779144" scope="local" type="part">Part 13.4</xref>. However, it should be noted that <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/4234_0.7.0.xml#_09a0cfcb-49e7-4656-a327-9fbd0dbd1672" id="_bcc600ed-f5f9-4e31-b801-95af151779e8" scope="local" type="part">Part 13.4</xref> does not apply in all States and Territories.</li><li>12.4.3(a) requires the internal faces of masonry chimneys to be parged with a mortar to protect masonry elements and mortar beds from the corrosive by-products of combustion.</li></ul></callout></clause>